HR-TEM monograph shows that the mean size of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs is 1.37 ± 0.48 nm, and displays spherical shape (Fig. 1

                        ). Meanwhile, Fig. 1c shows that the high magnified crystalline nature of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs with lattice fringe spacing (0.12 nm), which can be well matched with the (111) reflection of face centred cubic (fcc) of Au. The dynamic light scattering (DLS) data demonstrate that La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs are well dispersed in water with an average hydrodynamic diameter of 4.65 ± 1.3 nm (Fig. S2a of Supporting Information). The as-fabricated La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs exhibit the maximum absorbance at 342 nm (Fig. 3
                        ). The absorbance spectrum of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs showed a strong absorption band in the UV region, which is due to the distinctive electronic transition. The absence of surface plasmon resonance band at 520 nm confirms the generation of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs with ultra-small size < 3.0 nm. Upon excitation at 323 nm, La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs exhibit a strong emission peak at 652 nm with the QY of 18.2% (Fig. 3). Furthermore, the emission spectra of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs were measured by exciting at different wavelengths from 280 to 440 nm (Fig. S3 of Supporting Information), thereby facilitating to know the maximum emission intensity of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs. The brown solution of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs emitted a strong red fluorescence under UV light irradiation at 365 nm (Inset of Fig. 3). To investigate the surface state, La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs were characterized by X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS). Figs. S4 and S5 of Supporting Information showed that the XPS data of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs. The XPS spectrum of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs showed the binding energies at 94.5 and 90.9 eV, which correspond to Au 4f5/2 and Au 4f7/2, respectively. The photoelectron peaks at 291.5, 406.2 and 539.1, eV belong to the binding energies for carbon, nitrogen and oxygen, which are generated from La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs (Fig. S5 of Supporting Information). Typical XPS spectrum of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs showed that the photoelectron peaks at 843.8 and 841.6 eV, which are belonged to 3d3/2 and 3d5/2 states of La3+ ion. The formation of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs could also be confirmed by studying Fourier transform infrared (FTIR) spectroscopy since the structure of BSA is sensitive to the temperature and to the addition metal ions. As a result, the structure of BSA is drastically changed due to the formation of AuNCs. The absorption peaks at 1680 cm−1, (amide I, CO stretch vibration) and 1380 cm−1 (amide III, CN stretch vibration) were noticed in pure BSA (Fig. S6 of Supporting Information). However, the above characteristic peaks were slightly shifted with decreasing intensity, revealing the formation of bonds between Au3+ ion and BSA, which favors for the reduction of Au3+ ion to Au0 atom. These spectral characteristics illustrated that the formation of La3+ ion-BSA-AuNCs.
